Controversial SuperSport soccer commentator Baba Mthethwa is in trouble with the law after allegedly failing to pay a hefty bill that includes expensive alcohol and food at a swanky Joburg hotel. The Four Seasons Hotel, also known as the Westcliff Hotel, has gone to court to force the Sesotho commentator to cough up more than R60,000 he allegedly owes it. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD